- What is a server: A computer or program that provides data and functionality to other devices (clients).
- What is the role of the domain name: It provides a human-readable address (like foobar.com) mapped to an IP address.
- What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com: It is typically a CNAME record pointing to the root domain, or an A record pointing directly to the IP.
- What is the role of the web server: To serve static content (HTML, CSS, JS) via HTTP requests (e.g., Nginx).
- What is the role of the application server: To execute dynamic business logic and application code.
- What is the role of the database: To store, manage, and retrieve structured data (e.g., MySQL).
- What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user: TCP/IP and HTTP protocols.

Issues:
- SPOF: There is a Single Point of Failure. If this one server crashes, the entire website goes down.
- Downtime when maintenance needed: Restarting the web server or deploying code requires stopping the service, causing downtime.
- Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic: A single server has limited hardware resources (CPU/RAM) and will crash under heavy load.
